"Red vs. Blue is a mini battle game of Minecraft. The players of the servers would be randomly assigned to red/blue team to PVP battles. The team that first obtains a particular number of enemies will be the winner.

 Rules and procedures:
 1.The server host needs to set the server capacity (which must be even) and the winning condition (i.e., the number of enemies you kill);
 2. Waiting for other players to join your server, after it's full, click “start” to begin;
 3. All players in the server are divided randomly into two teams: Red Team and Blue Team. The nicknames of each team players are distinguished by the color of red and blue; You will be reminded of which team you belong to when the game starts to count down;
 4.During the game, killing an enemy player is counted as 1 kill; Killing a team player is counted as 1 manslaughter; Being killed by an enemy / team player is counted as 1 death; Dying accidentally (e.g., falling to death, being killed by monsters, etc.) is counted as 1 death;
 5. A reborn players can rejoin the battle until the end of the game or when the winner is identified;
 6. Each game lasts for a maximum of 25 minutes. The first team that kills a particular number of enemies in 25 minutes will be the winner.
 7. If neither team obtains the designated number of enemies in 25 minutes, whichever kills more number of enemies will be the winner; If two teams kill the same number of enemies, the game ends in a draw;
 8. If some player goes offline or leaves the server, the game continues; If all players of one team go offline or leave the server, the other team will be identified as the winner;"

