"1. The number of players is between 1 and 10; 
 2. Players can select a skill set before the game begins. They can use their skills during the game. Skills are subject to a cooling-off period; 
 3. At the start of the game, players will be delivered to the starting point. When the countdown is over, the game begins and players can start running forward; 
 4. During the race, players must cross over obstacles, jump and climb to pass through the race tracks; 
 5. There are plenty of Magicblocks on the race tracks. When players crush these Magicblocks, they receive a random boost of energy; 
 6. There are plenty of scattered Roadblock debris on the race tracks. Players can crush these Roadblock debris and place Roadblocks on the race tracks to unsettle other players; 
 7. The player who reaches the destination fastest and knocks on the Hall of Fame first is ranked the gold medalist. The second and third runners-up are the silver and bronze medalists. The game finishes 20 seconds after a gold medalist has been declared. Any player who fails to reach the destination and fails to knock on the Hall of Fame is considered not to have finished the race."
